Description: Dark grey limestone figure of a veiled woman or youth. Head fragment only, with flat back. The face is slim and triangular in shape, the mouth is small and slightly oblique; the eyes are large. The head is characterised by a great depth. Poor work; the eyes are roughly incised, the ears shapeless and large. The back is sawn flat.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Aphrodite (Naukratis), Context Φ8 (thought to be)
Curator's comments: Marked faintly Φ8 in pencil (likely Sanctuary of Aphrodite context 8). Parallels of heads from female figures found at Naukratis, dated between 600BC-575BC and 550BC-525BC (GR 1888,0601.29; Cambridge, Fitzwilliam Museum GR.2.1899; Nick 2006; Möller 2000, 157). Good, unpublished, parallel from Samos dated c.580/70BC (Jan Marc Henke 2013 pers. comm.).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (CD.055) (Phase 3)
